This paper deals with the study of Delaunay triangulations, which is a fundamental topic in computational geometry. The paper provides bounds on the number of higher order Delaunay triangulations, which is a problem related to computational geometry and discrete mathematics. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of expected values, which is related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper provides bounds on the number of triangulations, which is a problem related to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves the study of algorithms and data structures for triangulations, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
